cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.IR 

This paper involves the use of deep learning and radiomics features for the prediction of invasiveness of pulmonary adenocarcinomas using CT imaging. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of deep feature fusion networks, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper involves medical imaging and diagnosis, which could fall under cs.MED (Medical Imaging) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-categories.
